title: Zucchini and Brie Frittata
directions: Heat a large oven-proof, 10" skillet over medium heat. Melt butter, than add garlic and onion and cook about 3 minutes. Add 1 tablespoon olive oil and zucchini ribbons; cook until just softened, about 30 seconds to 1 minute.

Cut cherry tomatoes in half, set aside. In a medium mixing bowl whisk eggs and cream; season with 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Pour egg mixture, scallions, and parsley into skillet over medium-low heat. Cook until almost set, mixing slowly with a rubber spatula, 5 minutes. Mix in brie.
Heat broiler; place skillet under broiler and cook 2 to 3 minutes. (Watch carefully to prevent burning.)
Garnish with scallions and parsley. Serve immediately.
ingredients: 1 medium zucchini (about 1 lb.), trimmed and sliced lengthwise on mandoline
2 c. cherry tomatoes, cut in half
1/4 c. chopped scallion, plus more for garnish
1/4 c. chopped parsley, plus more for garnish
1/2 lb. brie, cut into 1" squares (1/4" thick)
